        {
            "text": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Recently, using a sample of 225.3\u00d710 6 J/\u03c8 events 9 collected with BESIII detector 10 at BEPCII, 11 the decay of J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b33(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) was analyzed, 12 and the X(1840) was observed in the 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) mass spectrum with a statistical significance of 7.6\u03c3. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) invariant mass spectrum is shown in Fig. 1, where the X(1840) can be clearly seen. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 52,
                    "end": 58,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The parameters of the X(1840) are extracted by an unbinned maximum likelihood fit. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "In the fit, the background is described by two contributions: the contribution from J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03c0 0 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) and the contribution from other sources. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The contribution from J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03c0 0 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) is determined from MC simulation and fixed in the fit (shown by the dash-dotted line in Fig. 2). ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 132,
                    "end": 139,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 2)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The other contribution is described by a third-order polynomial. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The signal is described by a Breit-Wigner function modified with the effects of the detection efficiency, the detector resolution, and the phase space factor. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The fit result is shown in Fig. 2  \u0393 = 83 \u00b1 14 \u00b1 11 MeV, respectively; the product branching fraction of the X(1840) is B(J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3X(1840)) \u00d7 B(X(1840) \u2192 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 )) = (2.44 \u00b1 0.36 +0.60 \u22120.74 ) \u00d7 10 \u22125 . ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 27,
                    "end": 33,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In these results, the first errors are statistical and the second errors are systematic. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 3 shows the comparisons of the X(1840) with other observations at BESIII. ",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 8,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Figure 3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "12 The comparisons indicate that at present one can not distinguish whether the X(1840) is a new state or the signal of a 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) decay mode of an existing state.",
            "section": "Observation of the X(1840)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
