        {
            "text": "Summary",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "With a sample of 225.3 \u00d7 10 6 J/\u03c8 events collected at BESIII, the decay of J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b33(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) was analyzed. ",
            "section": "Summary",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "12 The X(1840) was observed in the 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) invariant mass spectrum. ",
            "section": "Summary",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "12"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The mass, width and product branching fraction of the X(1840) are M = 1842.2 \u00b1 4.2 +7.1 \u22122.6 MeV/c 2 , \u0393 = 83 \u00b1 14 \u00b1 11 MeV and B(J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3X(1840)) \u00d7 B(X(1840) \u2192 3(\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 )) = (2.44 \u00b1 0.36 +0.60 \u22120.74 ) \u00d7 10 \u22125 , respectively. ",
            "section": "Summary",
